data.chText: 眨一只眼，眨眼示意（尤指使眼色或表示开玩笑）
data.enText: to close one eye and open it again quickly, especially as a private signal to sb, or to show sth is a joke

data.chText: 他冲她眨了眨眼，她便知道他的想法和她一样。
data.enText: He winked at her and she knew he was thinking the same thing that she was.

data.chText: 闪烁；明灭
data.enText: to shine with an unsteady light; to flash on and off

data.chText: 我们看见船在远方忽明忽暗地闪着灯光。
data.enText: We could see the lights of the ship winking in the distance.
wink at sth

data.chText: （尤指对坏事）视而不见；睁一只眼闭一只眼
data.enText: to pretend that you have not noticed sth, especially sth bad or illegal

data.chText: 眨一只眼；眨眼示意；眼色
data.enText: an act of winking , especially as a signal to sb

data.chText: 他向她会意地眨了一下眼睛。
data.enText: He gave her a knowing wink.
not get/have a wink of sleep
not sleep a wink

data.chText: 没合一下眼；不能入睡
data.enText: to not be able to sleep

data.chText: 我昨天一夜都没合眼。
data.enText: I didn't get a wink of sleep last night.

data.chText: 我几乎连个盹都没打。
data.enText: I hardly slept a wink.
a nod and a wink
a nod is as good as a wink

data.chText: 一点就懂；（心有灵犀）一点通
data.enText: used to say that a suggestion or a hint will be understood, without anything more being said

data.chText: 每件事只靠点拨一下就能办妥了。
data.enText: Everything could be done by a nod and a wink.
nudge nudge, wink wink
a nudge and a wink

data.chText: （暗指与性行为有关的事）眉来眼去
data.enText: used to suggest sth to do with sex without actually saying it

data.chText: 他们长期厮混在一起，卿卿我我的。
data.enText: They've been spending a lot of time together, nudge nudge, wink wink.
tip sb the wink
tip the wink to sb

data.chText: 给某人密送情报
data.enText: to give sb secret information that they can use to gain an advantage for themselves

tr: a reflex that closes and opens the eyes rapidly
closing one eye quickly as a signal
a very short time (as the time it takes the eye to blink or the heart to beat)
example: if I had the chance I'd do it in a flash
The TV announcer never seems to blink

tr: force to go away by blinking

value.def: When you wink at someone, you look towards them and close one eye very briefly, usually as a signal that something is a joke or a secret.

example.tran: 布赖恩向他的准新娘使了个眼色。

example.ex: He smiled, winked and nodded, giving his seal of approval.
example.tran: 他笑了，使了个眼色，然后点点头表示同意。

value.def: If a lamp winks, it shines or reflects light in short flashes.

example.ex: From the hotel window, they could see lights winking on the bay.
example.tran: 透过宾馆的窗子，他们能看见海湾一带灯光摇曳。

value.def: If you say that you did not sleep a wink or did not get a wink of sleep, you mean that you tried to go to sleep but could not.

example.ex: I didn't get a wink of sleep on the aeroplane.
example.tran: 我在飞机上没合一下眼。

trans: 故意忽视；假装没看见；纵容；使眼色；假装看不见
